e for this item. \n\no  A dash indicates \u201cno information.\u201d CMS expects dash use to be a rare occurrence. \n\nCoding Tips \n\n\u2022  Nonsensical responses, incorrect answers, and questions the patient chooses not to answer should be coded as \n\nzero. \no  The assessing clinician should track the reason for coding answers as zero because this information will \n\nbe used later for the coding of the summary score in C0500. \n\n\u2022  Rules for stopping the BIMS interview before it is complete:", "type": "Document"}}